The paper deals with polynomial approximations of ${\rm AC}^0$ circuits, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves the use of probabilistic polynomial algorithms and error analysis, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses lower bounds on polynomial approximations, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CR).
